 MBOMBELA – With it the choir celebrated the essence of yuletide across a host of musical styles, from a heavenly classical choral repertoire, to festive carols, wrapped in shiny new arrangements. The joyful performance full of Christmas cheer, lots of smiles and a touch of sentiment took place at Communio Church on Friday evening. ALSO READ: Mpumalanga Youth Choir sets ‘Mission Belgium’ in motion The choir tours at least twice a year, both nationally and internationally. It has just returned from a tour to the UK where it performed as a special act during The Lion King 20th anniversary celebrations at the Lyceum Theatre, with South African music legend, Lebo M. With the Noel Tour, the Drakensberg Boys Choir certainly spread the joy of Christmas. ALSO READ: Entertainment galore at the annual Uplands Festival 